File: Johannesburg residents have experienced several power cuts - due to planned and unplanned outages. JOHANNESBURG - Eskom is urging households to reduce electricity usage, to minimise the risk of load-shedding.  
The utility says the system is severely constrained and there is a high probability of load shedding. READ: Eskom implements load reduction A capacity shortage has been caused by the loss of multiple generation units and high-load losses. This is in addition to generation units already on planned maintenance. Eskom says teams are working around the clock to return these units to service as soon as possible.